Specialists from the department of agro-industrial policy, consumer market and entrepreneurship of the Gorlovka urban district administration held a working meeting with business entities selling non-food products. Today, April 11, specialists from the department of agro-industrial policy, consumer market and entrepreneurship of the Gorlovka urban district administration organized and held a working meeting with business entities selling non-food products.

At the meeting, business entities were informed:
- on the need for strict compliance with the rules for the sale of non-food products in accordance with the legislation of the Russian Federation;
- on mandatory registration before April 1, 2025 in the system of digital labeling and traceability of goods “Honest Sign” and the list of goods subject to labeling;
 - on holding a city competition “For the best landscaping of the territory.”

The meeting participants were provided with information materials in the form of memos on the issues raised at the meeting, as well as information about the ongoing two-month landscaping campaign, and instructions on compliance with the landscaping rules.
